1. Function: addNumbers
Description: Adds two numbers and returns the result.
Example:
Named Function
<pre><code>function addNumbers(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}</code></pre>
Arrow Function
<pre><code>const addNumbersArrow = (a, b) => a + b;</code></pre>
2. Function: multiplyNumbers
Description: Multiplies two numbers and returns the result.
Example:
Named Function
<pre><code>function multiplyNumbers(a, b) {
  return a * b;
}</code></pre>
Arrow Function
<pre><code>const multiplyNumbersArrow = (a, b) => a * b;</code></pre>
3. Function: findMax
Description: Finds the maximum number from an array of numbers and returns it.
Example:
<pre><code>function findMax(numbers) {
  return Math.max(...numbers);
}</code></pre>
Arrow Function
<pre><code>const findMaxArrow = (numbers) => Math.max(...numbers);</code></pre>
4. Function: isPalindrome
Description: Checks if a given string is a palindrome and returns a boolean value.
Example:
<pre><code>function isPalindrome(str) {
  const reversed = str.split('').reverse().join('');
  return str === reversed;
}</code></pre>
Arrow Function
<pre><code>const isPalindromeArrow = (str) => {
  const reversed = str.split('').reverse().join('');
  return str === reversed;
};</code></pre>

1. Function: reverseString
Description: Reverses a given string and returns the result.
Example:
Named Function
<pre><code>function reverseString(str) {
  return str.split('').reverse().join('');
}</code></pre>
Arrow Function
<pre><code>const reverseStringArrow = (str) => str.split('').reverse().join('');</code></pre>
2. Function: calculateFactorial
Description: Calculates the factorial of a given number.
Example:
Named Function
<pre><code>function calculateFactorial(n) {
  if (n === 0 || n === 1) {
    return 1;
  }
  return n * calculateFactorial(n - 1);
}</code></pre>
Arrow Function
<pre><code>const calculateFactorialArrow = (n) => (n === 0 || n === 1) ? 1 : n * calculateFactorialArrow(n - 1);</code></pre>
